1
00:00:02,850 --> 00:00:03,800
[ Splash! ]

2
00:00:05,370 --> 00:00:06,490
[ Otters squeal ]

3
00:00:08,290 --> 00:00:09,120
[ Birds chirp ]

4
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:10,380
Ptoo! Ptoo!

5
00:00:12,390 --> 00:00:14,510
Not too fast, now,
Angel bunny.

6
00:00:14,560 --> 00:00:16,210
You don't want to get
a tummy ache.

7
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:20,920
[ Chuckles ]

8
00:00:20,960 --> 00:00:23,690
You really should eat more
than that, don't you think?

9
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:24,570
[ Boing! Boing! Boing! ]

10
00:00:25,520 --> 00:00:26,850
It's not playtime yet.

11
00:00:26,930 --> 00:00:29,440
[ Boing! Boing! Boing! ]

12
00:00:29,690 --> 00:00:30,880
I know
you want to run,

13
00:00:30,910 --> 00:00:33,220
But just
three more bites.

14
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:34,300
Two more bites?

15
00:00:35,580 --> 00:00:36,760
One more bite?

16
00:00:37,430 --> 00:00:39,040
Pretty please?

17
00:00:39,290 --> 00:00:40,010
[ Sighs ]

18
00:00:41,630 --> 00:00:43,570
[ Coughing ]
oh, goodness.

19
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:44,770
Are you okay?

20
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:46,530
Are you coughing

21
00:00:46,560 --> 00:00:48,510
Because there's a carrot
stuck in your throat?

22
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:51,030
Because you need
some water?

23
00:00:51,150 --> 00:00:52,560
[ Coughing loudly ]

24
00:00:53,570 --> 00:00:54,160
[ Gasps ]

25
00:00:54,350 --> 00:00:57,680
Because of that giant cloud
of scary, black smoke?

26
00:00:59,330 --> 00:01:01,680
I'll take that as a...
yes.

27
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:09,500
Hard of Hearing subtitles
by YayPonies
https://yp1.yayponies.no/

28
00:01:41,420 --> 00:01:43,330
Help! Help!

29
00:01:43,870 --> 00:01:44,460
Please?

30
00:01:44,970 --> 00:01:45,680
Help!

31
00:01:46,100 --> 00:01:48,810
There's -- There's a horrible
cloud of smoke.

32
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:51,910
It's headed this way,
and -- Aah!

33
00:01:52,830 --> 00:01:54,810
Don't be such
a scaredy-Pony.

34
00:01:54,910 --> 00:01:58,410
It's just me, future Equestria
ball-Bouncing record holder.

35
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:00,280
146, 147...

36
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:02,640
this calls
for a celebration!

37
00:02:02,730 --> 00:02:06,300
Oh, no, Pinkie Pie.
This is no time for celebration.

38
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:08,200
This is a time for panic,
for --

39
00:02:08,270 --> 00:02:10,400
Ooh!
I'm gonna need balloons!

40
00:02:10,450 --> 00:02:12,620
One for every pony
in Ponyville.

41
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:14,270
There's -- There's smoke,

42
00:02:14,420 --> 00:02:16,750
And -- And where there's smoke,
there's fire, and --

43
00:02:16,780 --> 00:02:17,720
Let's see!

44
00:02:17,780 --> 00:02:20,850
That's
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6...

45
00:02:20,910 --> 00:02:22,790
154, 155...
no, wait.

46
00:02:22,930 --> 00:02:23,650
7...

47
00:02:24,290 --> 00:02:25,230
Pinkie Pie!

48
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,720
Now I have to
start over.

49
00:02:26,960 --> 00:02:29,360
We're all gonna have to
start over

50
00:02:29,540 --> 00:02:30,410
In a new village,

51
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:32,190
'Cause ours
is gonna be --

52
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:33,800
Hey, Rainbow Dash,
wait up!

53
00:02:33,990 --> 00:02:36,380
Oh, please.
This is an emergency.

54
00:02:36,620 --> 00:02:38,020
I-I need every pony
to --

55
00:02:38,060 --> 00:02:38,940
Listen up!

56
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:42,410
Smoke is spreading
over all of Equestria.

57
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:43,600
What?!
Oh, no!
Oh, no!

58
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:45,880
That's what i've
been trying to --

59
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:46,920
Pony:
but don't worry.

60
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:49,350
I've just received a letter
from princess Celestia

61
00:02:49,380 --> 00:02:51,530
Informing me that it is not
coming from a fire.

62
00:02:51,730 --> 00:02:53,500
Oh, thank goodness.

63
00:02:53,810 --> 00:02:55,320
Pony:
it's coming from a dragon.

64
00:02:55,380 --> 00:02:56,350
[ All gasp ]

65
00:02:56,690 --> 00:02:59,020
A...d-D-Dragon?

66
00:03:00,610 --> 00:03:03,100
Applejack: what in the name
of all things cinnamon swirl

67
00:03:03,130 --> 00:03:05,480
Is a full-Grown dragon
doing here in Equestria?

68
00:03:05,540 --> 00:03:06,150
Sleeping.

69
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:07,340
Huh?
Huh?Huh?
Huh?

70
00:03:07,630 --> 00:03:10,240
According to princess Celestia,
he's taking a nap.

71
00:03:10,950 --> 00:03:12,990
His snoring is what's causing
all this smoke.

72
00:03:13,410 --> 00:03:14,820
He should really see
a doctor.

73
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:16,530
That doesn't sound healthy
at all.

74
00:03:16,890 --> 00:03:19,630
Well, at least he's not
snoring fire.

75
00:03:20,050 --> 00:03:21,730
What are we meant to do
about it?

76
00:03:21,890 --> 00:03:23,600
Rainbow Dash: I'll tell you
what we're meant to do --

77
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:24,700
Give him the boot!

78
00:03:24,860 --> 00:03:25,590
Take that!
[ Tinkling ]

79
00:03:26,990 --> 00:03:27,730
And that!
[ Tinkling ]

80
00:03:30,050 --> 00:03:33,620
We need to encourage him
to take a nap somewhere else.

81
00:03:34,170 --> 00:03:36,090
Princess Celestia
has given us this mission,

82
00:03:36,140 --> 00:03:37,420
And we must not fail.

83
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:39,680
If we do, Equestria
will be covered in smoke

84
00:03:39,740 --> 00:03:41,110
For the next 100 years.

85
00:03:41,180 --> 00:03:42,420
[ Gasps ]
[ scoffs ]

86
00:03:42,540 --> 00:03:44,530
Talk about getting
your beauty sleep.

87
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:47,450
All right, everypony, I need you
to gather supplies quickly.

88
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:49,170
We've got a long journey
ahead of us.

89
00:03:49,210 --> 00:03:50,950
Let's meet back here
in less than an hour.

90
00:03:51,070 --> 00:03:52,860
Okay, girls,
you heard her!

91
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:54,890
The fate of Equestria
is in our hooves.

92
00:03:55,060 --> 00:03:57,200
Do we have
what it takes?!

93
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:59,010
Yeah!
You betcha!
We can do it!

94
00:03:59,370 --> 00:04:00,900
Yeah, we can do it!

95
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:03,100
Um...actually...

96
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:10,650
rrarrr!

97
00:04:18,170 --> 00:04:19,290
Hyah!

98
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:22,720
[ Cheer! ]

99
00:04:22,860 --> 00:04:24,410
[ Giggles ]

100
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:25,300
Oh, I mean...

101
00:04:25,530 --> 00:04:26,770
grrr!

102
00:04:31,770 --> 00:04:32,640
Ew!

103
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,040
Much better.

104
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,180
Onward!

105
00:04:39,010 --> 00:04:40,840
[Door hinges creak, door slams]
[ squeals ]

106
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:44,430
Let's go!

107
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,940
Um...
let's...not?

108
00:04:47,090 --> 00:04:48,780
[ Squeals nervously ]

109
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,320
All right, girls,
listen up.

110
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,150
I'm mapping out
the fastest route,

111
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,530
But we've all got to keep
a good pace

112
00:04:55,570 --> 00:04:57,730
If we expect to make it up
the mountain by nightfall.

113
00:04:58,190 --> 00:04:59,730
M-Mountain?

114
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:02,190
The dragon is in that cave
at the very top.

115
00:05:02,390 --> 00:05:03,460
Looks pretty cold
up there.

116
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:05,050
You bet it is.

117
00:05:05,310 --> 00:05:07,500
The higher you go,
the chillier it gets.

118
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:09,300
Good thing
I brought my scarf.

119
00:05:10,810 --> 00:05:12,210
Ooh! Pretty!

120
00:05:13,130 --> 00:05:14,010
[ Chuckles ]

121
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:14,730
Oh, yeah.

122
00:05:15,010 --> 00:05:17,100
That'll keep you
nice and cozy.

123
00:05:21,500 --> 00:05:21,890
[ Gulp! ]

124
00:05:24,430 --> 00:05:26,880
Fluttershy:
um, excuse me. Twilight?

125
00:05:27,190 --> 00:05:28,430
I know you're busy,
but --

126
00:05:28,510 --> 00:05:29,230
Uh-Huh.

127
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:30,930
Well,
we could go this way.

128
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:32,750
But if I could just have
a second --

129
00:05:32,780 --> 00:05:35,400
Uh-Huh.
No, we want to avoid that.

130
00:05:36,380 --> 00:05:39,320
So, um, i-I was thinking
that, um,

131
00:05:39,790 --> 00:05:42,810
Maybe I should
just stay here in Ponyville.

132
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:43,960
Uh-Huh.

133
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:45,410
Oh, good!

134
00:05:45,730 --> 00:05:46,810
I'll stay here and --

135
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,610
Wait!
You have to come.

136
00:05:48,860 --> 00:05:51,340
Your way with wild animals
will surely come in handy.

137
00:05:51,970 --> 00:05:53,380
I don't think I --

138
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,450
Oh, and don't worry
about your little
friends in the meadow.

139
00:05:55,650 --> 00:05:57,210
Spike's got it covered
while you're gone.

140
00:05:57,330 --> 00:05:58,590
You can count on me.

141
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:00,480
Ohh!

142
00:06:01,380 --> 00:06:02,370
Hey! Hey!

143
00:06:02,710 --> 00:06:03,350
Wait!

144
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:05,290
I don't really think
he's up to the task.

145
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:05,970
Maybe...

146
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:08,140
but...but...

147
00:06:08,670 --> 00:06:09,100
[ squeals ]

148
00:06:09,690 --> 00:06:12,000
Are you sure you want Fluttershy
to come along?

149
00:06:12,130 --> 00:06:14,350
I mean, that pony's afraid
of her own shadow.

150
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,560
She's just gonna
slow us down.

151
00:06:16,780 --> 00:06:18,170
Oh, she's just
a little nervous.

152
00:06:18,460 --> 00:06:20,590
Once we get going,
I'm sure she'll be fine.

153
00:06:20,810 --> 00:06:21,470
Fluttershy: oh!

154
00:06:21,660 --> 00:06:23,340
[ Whiffle! ]

155
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:27,740
All right, girls.

156
00:06:28,990 --> 00:06:29,790
Move out.

157
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:32,140
But...but...

158
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:34,430
[ squeals ]

159
00:06:37,730 --> 00:06:40,940
[ Dragon snoring loudly ]

160
00:06:41,050 --> 00:06:41,970
[ Gasps ]

161
00:06:42,070 --> 00:06:43,400
Whoa!
What was that?

162
00:06:43,440 --> 00:06:46,250
That is what it sounds like
when a dragon snores.

163
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,090
It's -- It's so...

164
00:06:49,870 --> 00:06:50,380
high.

165
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:52,510
Well,
it is a mountain.

166
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,710
I'm gonna fly up there
and check it out!

167
00:06:54,750 --> 00:06:55,760
[ Creak! ]
[ Grunts ]

168
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:57,110
Hold on, now.

169
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:58,930
I think we should
all go up together.

170
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,560
Safety in numbers
and all.

171
00:07:01,290 --> 00:07:03,100
Oh, all right.

172
00:07:04,840 --> 00:07:08,450
I hear the only thing
that sparkles more
than a dragon's scales

173
00:07:08,590 --> 00:07:10,990
Are the jewels they use
to build their nests.

174
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:11,840
Ooh!

175
00:07:12,060 --> 00:07:13,250
If I play
my cards right,

176
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:15,640
I might be able to convince him
to part with a few.

177
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:18,190
"Welcome to my cave,
Rarity.

178
00:07:18,350 --> 00:07:19,600
"Care for a diamond?

179
00:07:19,890 --> 00:07:22,000
Rrarrr!"

180
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:24,730
[ Laughter ]

181
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:27,530
Girls!
This is no laughing matter.

182
00:07:28,050 --> 00:07:30,440
Fluttershy, you're the expert
on wild creatures.

183
00:07:30,620 --> 00:07:32,510
What do you think the dragon
will be like?

184
00:07:34,160 --> 00:07:34,780
Fluttershy?

185
00:07:35,530 --> 00:07:39,340
Hey, what are you waiting for --
An invitation?

186
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:41,260
Ooh! I think I have one
in my bag.

187
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:42,210
[ Cheer! ]

188
00:07:43,890 --> 00:07:46,040
I-It's so...so...

189
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,440
steep.

190
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,250
Well, it is a cliff.

191
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:52,490
You could just --
Oh, I don't know -- Fly up here.

192
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,740
Come on, Fluttershy,
you can do it!

193
00:07:54,860 --> 00:07:56,110
Flap those wings.

194
00:07:56,170 --> 00:07:57,770
Uh...okay.

195
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,620
[ Inhales deeply ]

196
00:08:01,930 --> 00:08:04,670
[ Dragon snoring loudly ]

197
00:08:07,650 --> 00:08:08,800
Ohh! Uhh!

198
00:08:09,230 --> 00:08:10,140
[ Groans ]

199
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:12,290
[ Grunting ]

200
00:08:12,370 --> 00:08:14,390
[ Sighs ]
we don't have time for this.

201
00:08:15,890 --> 00:08:16,820
What are you doing?

202
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:18,530
I'll need this
if I'm gonna take her

203
00:08:18,550 --> 00:08:19,630
Around the mountain
another way.

204
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:20,630
Ohh!

205
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:22,420
Around
the mountain?

206
00:08:23,110 --> 00:08:25,040
That's gonna take
them forever.

207
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:26,260
[ Squeals ]

208
00:08:26,860 --> 00:08:29,610
[ Dragon snoring loudly ]

209
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,230
Don't worry, twi.

210
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:33,790
We'll be there
lickety-Split.

211
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:40,070
Whoo-Hoo!
I win again!

212
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:42,780
[ Sighs ]
that's 35 games in a row.

213
00:08:43,230 --> 00:08:44,430
Best of 71?

214
00:08:45,890 --> 00:08:47,490
[ Applejack
breathing heavily ]

215
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:49,820
We...made...it.

216
00:08:50,970 --> 00:08:53,020
Told you it was gonna
take them forever.

217
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:05,470
[ Gulp! ]

218
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,840
Your turn,
Fluttershy.

219
00:09:09,280 --> 00:09:11,840
But it's so wide.

220
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:13,150
Come on, Fluttershy.

221
00:09:13,210 --> 00:09:15,170
We should be
much farther along by now.

222
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:17,410
You could just
leap on over.

223
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:18,050
I --

224
00:09:18,270 --> 00:09:21,280
[ Dragon snoring loudly ]

225
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:22,190
I don't know.

226
00:09:23,130 --> 00:09:24,630
There's nothing
to be afraid of.

227
00:09:24,660 --> 00:09:26,100
It's just
a hop, skip, and a jump!

228
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:27,490
See?

229
00:09:27,890 --> 00:09:30,190
* it's not very far,
just move your little rump *

230
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:32,780
* you can make it if you try
with a hop, skip, and jump *

231
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:34,140
We don't have time
for this.

232
00:09:34,510 --> 00:09:36,810
* a hop, skip, and a jump,
just move your little rump *

233
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,560
* a hop, skip, and jump,
a hop, skip, and jump *

234
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,130
* a hop, skip, and jump,
a hop, skip, and jump *

235
00:09:40,170 --> 00:09:41,090
* a hop, skip, and jump

236
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,430
Okay.

237
00:09:42,770 --> 00:09:43,820
Here I go.

238
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,120
A hop...

239
00:09:45,910 --> 00:09:47,610
that's it.
You got it.
Almost there.

240
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:48,720
Skip...

241
00:09:49,290 --> 00:09:50,650
just don't look down.

242
00:09:53,550 --> 00:09:54,060
Aah!

243
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:58,490
[ Wind howling ]

244
00:09:58,570 --> 00:09:59,880
[ Groans ]

245
00:10:03,990 --> 00:10:05,580
I guess
I forgot to jump.

246
00:10:10,470 --> 00:10:11,550
Twilight Sparkle:
let's keep it down.

247
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:12,750
According to my map,

248
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,220
We're entering
an avalanche zone.

249
00:10:14,510 --> 00:10:16,940
The smallest peep
could cause a huge rockslide.

250
00:10:18,620 --> 00:10:21,120
An --
An ava-- Ava--

251
00:10:21,150 --> 00:10:21,680
Shh!

252
00:10:22,050 --> 00:10:24,920
[ Wind howling ]

253
00:10:34,010 --> 00:10:34,410
[ Poink! ]

254
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:36,850
[ Echoing ] avala--

255
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:42,030
[ All sigh ]

256
00:10:43,210 --> 00:10:45,810
[ Loud rumbling ]

257
00:10:50,650 --> 00:10:52,730
Avalanche!
Avalanche!
Avalanche!
Avalanche!

258
00:10:52,850 --> 00:10:55,050
[ All screaming ]

259
00:11:08,270 --> 00:11:09,340
Oh, no!

260
00:11:09,410 --> 00:11:10,430
Help! Oh!

261
00:11:12,530 --> 00:11:14,410
[ All coughing ]

262
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,270
Oh, my.

263
00:11:16,690 --> 00:11:17,950
Everypony okay?

264
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:20,090
Thanks to you,
I am.

265
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:23,760
Ugh! Blech!

266
00:11:23,790 --> 00:11:25,900
Whoo-Hoo!
Let's do it again!

267
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:26,860
[ Scoffs ]

268
00:11:27,150 --> 00:11:30,560
This is why a girl
always packs extra accessories.

269
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:35,740
Oh, please tell me I brought
the tiara that goes with this.

270
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,020
Uh, I think we got
bigger problems

271
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:40,830
Than making sure our hair bows
match our horseshoes.

272
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:43,770
[ Sighs ]
sorry.

273
00:11:44,130 --> 00:11:46,580
Ah, no big whoop,
sugar cube.

274
00:11:46,830 --> 00:11:47,410
Yeah.

275
00:11:47,580 --> 00:11:51,280
We'll just have to [sighs]
climb over.

276
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:57,360
[ All grunting, moaning ]

277
00:12:02,410 --> 00:12:03,040
[ Sighs ]

278
00:12:03,210 --> 00:12:03,840
[ Squeals ]

279
00:12:04,810 --> 00:12:05,410
Aah!

280
00:12:05,540 --> 00:12:06,270
Aah!

281
00:12:06,430 --> 00:12:07,660
[ Crash! ]

282
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:11,200
My apologies.

283
00:12:11,530 --> 00:12:13,180
Not your fault.

284
00:12:17,910 --> 00:12:20,760
Still think it was a good idea
to bring Fluttershy along?

285
00:12:21,310 --> 00:12:22,680
We're about to
find out.

286
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,180
We're here.

287
00:12:30,780 --> 00:12:33,660
Rainbow Dash, you'll use
your wings to clear the smoke.

288
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:34,450
Mm-Hmm.

289
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:36,990
Rarity and Pinkie Pie,

290
00:12:37,170 --> 00:12:38,960
You create a diversion
to distract the dragon

291
00:12:38,990 --> 00:12:40,510
If things get a little hairy
in there.

292
00:12:41,330 --> 00:12:45,260
[ Squeaking ]

293
00:12:45,690 --> 00:12:47,310
Applejack,
you're ready with the apples

294
00:12:47,340 --> 00:12:48,750
In case he decides
to attack.

295
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:54,930
But it shouldn't come to that
because Fluttershy

296
00:12:54,970 --> 00:12:56,610
Will do what she needs to do
to wake him up.

297
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:58,750
And between the two of us,
we should be able

298
00:12:58,770 --> 00:13:00,700
To get him to understand
why he needs to go.

299
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,030
Is everypony ready?

300
00:13:02,540 --> 00:13:03,550
Mm-Hmm!
Mm-Hmm!
Mm-Hmm!
Mm-Hmm!

301
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:07,720
Okay, then.
We're going in.

302
00:13:09,060 --> 00:13:09,730
So...

303
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:12,510
what is the best way
to wake up a sleeping dragon

304
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,010
Without upsetting him?

305
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:15,340
Fluttershy?

306
00:13:15,970 --> 00:13:17,700
Oh, come on.

307
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:18,710
Come on!

308
00:13:19,310 --> 00:13:19,710
[ Grunts ]

309
00:13:20,030 --> 00:13:21,060
We have to do this.

310
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:21,920
[ Grunts ]

311
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:22,750
Now!

312
00:13:24,170 --> 00:13:26,140
Every [grunts]
second longer

313
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,960
That dragon [grunts]
sleeps

314
00:13:27,990 --> 00:13:30,350
Is another [grunts] acre
of Equestria

315
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:33,690
That is covered
in [grunts] smoke.

316
00:13:34,850 --> 00:13:36,280
I...i...

317
00:13:37,060 --> 00:13:38,560
I can't go in the cave.

318
00:13:38,610 --> 00:13:39,730
[ All groan ]

319
00:13:40,430 --> 00:13:41,410
Oh, great!

320
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:43,430
She's scared
of caves now, too.

321
00:13:43,570 --> 00:13:45,210
I'm not scared
of caves.

322
00:13:45,430 --> 00:13:46,840
I'm scared of dr...

323
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:48,620
what's that,
sugar cube?

324
00:13:48,810 --> 00:13:50,890
I'm scared of drag...

325
00:13:51,690 --> 00:13:52,170
what?

326
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,610
I'm scared of dragons!

327
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:56,790
[ Dragon snoring loudly ]

328
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:57,520
[ Squeals ]

329
00:13:58,030 --> 00:14:00,430
[ All coughing ]

330
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:05,780
But, Fluttershy,
you have a wonderful talent

331
00:14:05,820 --> 00:14:07,870
Dealing with all kinds
of animals.

332
00:14:08,170 --> 00:14:10,890
Yes, because
they're not dragons.

333
00:14:10,990 --> 00:14:12,180
Oh, come on!

334
00:14:12,450 --> 00:14:14,750
We've seen you walk right up
to a horrible manticore

335
00:14:14,780 --> 00:14:15,850
Like it was nothing.

336
00:14:15,970 --> 00:14:18,640
Yes,
because he wasn't a dragon.

337
00:14:18,980 --> 00:14:21,320
Spike is a dragon.
You're not scared of him.

338
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:25,130
Yes, because he's not a huge,
gigantic, terrifying, enormous,

339
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:26,620
Teeth-Gnashing,
shark-Scale-Having,

340
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:27,840
Horn-Wearing,
smoke-Snoring,

341
00:14:27,880 --> 00:14:29,070
Could-Eat-A-Pony-In-One-Bite,

342
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:31,610
Totally all-Grown-Up dragon.

343
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:34,290
[ Dragon snoring loudly ]

344
00:14:34,390 --> 00:14:36,270
[ Whimpering ]

345
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,570
But if you're
so afraid of dragons,

346
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:39,920
Why didn't you
say something

347
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:41,720
Before we came
all the way up here?

348
00:14:42,050 --> 00:14:43,640
I was afraid to.

349
00:14:43,940 --> 00:14:44,880
Argh!

350
00:14:45,660 --> 00:14:47,570
All of us are scared
of that dragon.

351
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:48,960
I'm not!

352
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,110
Almost all of us
are scared of that dragon,

353
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:54,020
But we've got a job
to do.

354
00:14:54,290 --> 00:14:55,790
So get in there
with Twilight

355
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:57,090
And show her
what you're made of.

356
00:14:57,820 --> 00:14:59,490
I...i...

357
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:01,770
I just...

358
00:15:02,650 --> 00:15:03,470
can't.

359
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:05,780
Oh, Fluttershy.

360
00:15:08,770 --> 00:15:09,820
I'm going in.

361
00:15:10,570 --> 00:15:12,800
He probably just doesn't realize
what he's doing...

362
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:14,090
right?

363
00:15:14,620 --> 00:15:16,290
Oh, yeah.
Sure.
Easy-Peasy.
Of course.

364
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:17,850
If you say so.
[ Laughs ]

365
00:15:20,730 --> 00:15:22,060
Mr. Dragon?

366
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:26,410
[ Snoring loudly ]

367
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:30,330
Uh, excuse me?

368
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:31,980
[ Grumbles ]

369
00:15:32,780 --> 00:15:34,350
Mr. Dragon?

370
00:15:37,610 --> 00:15:40,000
Oh, good.
You're awake.

371
00:15:40,500 --> 00:15:42,200
Please allow me
to introduce myself.

372
00:15:42,530 --> 00:15:43,420
My name is Twilight...

373
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:47,320
[ groans, roars ]

374
00:15:47,410 --> 00:15:48,330
Ohh!

375
00:15:48,410 --> 00:15:49,190
[ Groans ]

376
00:15:49,370 --> 00:15:51,520
...Sparkle,
and my friends and i

377
00:15:51,540 --> 00:15:53,500
Are residents here
in Equestria.

378
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:54,850
[ Snorts ]

379
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,430
Ponyville,
to be exact.

380
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:57,580
We've come here to ask

381
00:15:57,630 --> 00:15:59,740
That you find another spot
to take your nap.

382
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:03,200
It's just that you seem to be
doing an awful lot of snoring,

383
00:16:03,550 --> 00:16:04,560
And every time you do,

384
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:06,130
You send out a terrible cloud
of smoke.

385
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:08,880
[ Snorts ]
[ coughing ]

386
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:12,690
Equestria simply can't survive
100 years in a dark haze.

387
00:16:12,990 --> 00:16:15,040
You understand,
don't you?

388
00:16:15,310 --> 00:16:22,370
[ Groaning ]

389
00:16:22,770 --> 00:16:24,820
So, you'll find
another place to sleep?

390
00:16:26,770 --> 00:16:28,290
[ Snoring loudly ]

391
00:16:28,330 --> 00:16:30,310
[ Coughing ]

392
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:34,320
[ Dragon snorts, all cough ]

393
00:16:34,430 --> 00:16:37,420
So much for [coughs]
persuading him.

394
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:39,710
Now what?

395
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:41,070
[ Clears throat ]

396
00:16:41,180 --> 00:16:42,600
Obviously,
this situation

397
00:16:42,630 --> 00:16:45,020
Just calls for a little
pony charm.

398
00:16:45,690 --> 00:16:47,070
Allow me, girls.

399
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:50,950
[ Singsong voice ]
I'm so sorry to interrupt.

400
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:51,570
[ Clears throat ]

401
00:16:52,130 --> 00:16:53,890
Uh, but I couldn't possibly
head back home

402
00:16:53,930 --> 00:16:56,930
Without mentioning
what handsome scales you have.

403
00:16:57,900 --> 00:17:00,290
And those scales
have to be hidden away

404
00:17:00,330 --> 00:17:02,960
In some silly cave
for 100 years?

405
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:05,060
[ Groans ]

406
00:17:05,260 --> 00:17:07,890
Personally, I think you should
skip the snoozing

407
00:17:07,950 --> 00:17:09,860
And be out there,
showing them off.

408
00:17:10,160 --> 00:17:10,720
[ Chuckles ]

409
00:17:11,070 --> 00:17:12,750
Obviously,
I would be more than happy

410
00:17:12,850 --> 00:17:14,570
To keep an eye on your jewels
while you're gone.

411
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:18,690
[ Roars ]

412
00:17:18,810 --> 00:17:19,640
Aah!

413
00:17:20,990 --> 00:17:23,310
I was this close
to getting that diamond.

414
00:17:23,660 --> 00:17:25,970
You mean,
"getting rid of that dragon"?

415
00:17:26,370 --> 00:17:28,140
Oh, yeah, sure.

416
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:29,730
[ Party horn blowing ]
Applejack:
what in tarnation?

417
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:34,240
Darling,
you look ridiculous.

418
00:17:34,490 --> 00:17:35,400
Exactly!

419
00:17:36,020 --> 00:17:38,760
Sharing a laugh is a surefire
way to get someone on your side.

420
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:39,600
Hi!

421
00:17:39,990 --> 00:17:41,580
[ Crash! ]

422
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,840
Apparently he doesn't like
laughing [chuckles]

423
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:47,130
Or sharing.

424
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:48,610
All right!
That's it!

425
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:51,090
We've tried persuasion,
charm,

426
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:53,230
Whatever it is
Pinkie Pie does.

427
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:54,350
[ Party horn blows ]

428
00:17:54,890 --> 00:17:57,950
It's time to stop wasting time!
I'm going in!

429
00:17:58,110 --> 00:17:59,520
Rainbow, no!
[ Zoom! ]

430
00:18:00,990 --> 00:18:02,200
Get out!

431
00:18:04,010 --> 00:18:06,670
Ah-Ah-Ah-Ah-Choo!

432
00:18:07,570 --> 00:18:08,720
[ Growls ]

433
00:18:08,860 --> 00:18:10,010
I'm...sorry.

434
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:12,070
[ Roars ]

435
00:18:12,110 --> 00:18:13,650
Wh-O-O-O-Oa!

436
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:14,970
[ Strike! ]

437
00:18:15,510 --> 00:18:16,160
[ Tweet! ]

438
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:17,280
Aah!
Whoa!

439
00:18:20,330 --> 00:18:21,570
[ Growling ]

440
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:22,380
[ Whimpering ]

441
00:18:22,490 --> 00:18:25,820
[ Roars ]

442
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:30,270
[ All groaning ]

443
00:18:39,660 --> 00:18:40,870
How dare you?

444
00:18:41,930 --> 00:18:44,160
How dare you!

445
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,290
Listen here, mister!

446
00:18:46,540 --> 00:18:47,650
Just because you're big

447
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,940
Doesn't mean you get to be
a bully!

448
00:18:50,290 --> 00:18:52,080
You may have huge teeth
and sharp scales

449
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:54,010
And snore smoke
and breathe fire,

450
00:18:54,150 --> 00:18:55,640
But you do not --

451
00:18:55,890 --> 00:19:00,030
I repeat --
You do not hurt my friends!!

452
00:19:01,120 --> 00:19:02,500
You got that?

453
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:04,810
[ Whimpers ]

454
00:19:05,150 --> 00:19:06,210
Well?

455
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:10,660
But that Rainbow one
kicked me.

456
00:19:12,340 --> 00:19:14,900
And I am very sorry
about that.

457
00:19:15,930 --> 00:19:18,880
But you're bigger than she is,
and you should know better.

458
00:19:19,310 --> 00:19:21,200
You should also know better
than to take a nap

459
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:23,090
Where your snoring can become
a health hazard

460
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,620
To other creatures.

461
00:19:25,360 --> 00:19:26,280
But I --

462
00:19:26,390 --> 00:19:28,710
Don't you "but i" me,
mister.

463
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:31,150
Now, what do you have to say
for yourself?

464
00:19:31,970 --> 00:19:35,950
I said, what do you have to say
for yourself?

465
00:19:36,490 --> 00:19:44,910
[ Sobbing loudly ]

466
00:19:45,310 --> 00:19:47,810
There, there.
No need to cry.

467
00:19:47,980 --> 00:19:49,470
You're not
a bad dragon.

468
00:19:49,610 --> 00:19:51,450
You just made
a bad decision.

469
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,090
Now,
go pack your things.

470
00:19:53,220 --> 00:19:55,450
You just need to find
a new place to sleep.

471
00:19:55,550 --> 00:19:56,250
That's all.

472
00:19:56,350 --> 00:19:58,710
[ All cheering ]
Fluttershy
to the rescue!

473
00:19:58,890 --> 00:20:01,320
You did it.
I knew you could do it.

474
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:15,280
[ Spike exhales sharply ]

475
00:20:15,700 --> 00:20:17,690
I said, come back here!

476
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:18,850
Ohh!

477
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:20,290
[ Creak! ]

478
00:20:20,910 --> 00:20:24,180
How does Fluttershy put up
with you furry, little things?

479
00:20:24,430 --> 00:20:25,250
Twilight Sparkle:
Spike?

480
00:20:26,010 --> 00:20:26,870
Take a letter.

481
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:29,710
[ Sighs ]
with pleasure.

482
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:32,600
"Dear princess Celestia,
I am happy to report

483
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:34,700
"That the dragon has departed
our fair country

484
00:20:35,030 --> 00:20:36,950
"And that it was
my good friend Fluttershy

485
00:20:36,990 --> 00:20:38,190
"Who convinced him to go.

486
00:20:38,390 --> 00:20:39,640
"This adventure
has taught me

487
00:20:39,690 --> 00:20:41,600
"To never lose faith
in your friends.

488
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:43,830
"They can be
an amazing source of strength

489
00:20:44,070 --> 00:20:46,980
"And can help you overcome
even your greatest fears.

490
00:20:47,370 --> 00:20:50,320
Always your faithful student,
Twilight Sparkle."

491
00:20:50,370 --> 00:20:52,780
Applejack: Twilight,
you got to come see this!

492
00:20:53,690 --> 00:20:56,010
She's just five away
from a new pony record.

493
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:58,420
347, 348...

494
00:20:58,490 --> 00:21:00,050
Pinkie Pie:
rrarrr!
Dragon!

495
00:21:00,080 --> 00:21:00,940
[ Bleats ]

496
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:05,350
[ Laughter ]

497
00:21:05,770 --> 00:21:08,210
Why are you laughing?
That awful dragon is back!

498
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:11,170
Rrarrr!

499
00:21:11,420 --> 00:21:13,370
Pinkie Pie,
you scared me!

500
00:21:13,870 --> 00:21:15,280
I mean, uh...

501
00:21:15,640 --> 00:21:18,350
you broke
my concentration.

502
00:21:19,590 --> 00:21:21,240
It's okay,
Rainbow Dash.

503
00:21:21,510 --> 00:21:24,110
Not eve pony
can be as brave as me.

504
00:21:24,320 --> 00:21:24,990
[ Exhales sharply ]

505
00:21:26,170 --> 00:21:26,570
[ Poink! ]

506
00:21:26,630 --> 00:21:27,660
Aah!
[ Bleats ]

507
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:31,280
[ Laughter ]

